Rating: 2
Obviously, I'm in the minority here, but I found it just OK. No citrus vinaigrette at our grocery, so made a simple lime vinaigrette (oil, lime juice, Dijon mustard, garlic, cumin, salt & pepper). I think that the vegetables would have been better chilled, fresh and crunchy rather than grilled, hot and soft -- hot food on lettuce tends to be a personal aversion of mine that DH does not share. Will try it that way next time, and will also look for one of the bottled dressings listed here. Perhaps my lime vinaigrette was to blame for the lukewarm response.

